C++17 file+STL based project

-----------------------------------------
STL Short Notes

Containers
    vector          – Dynamic array, fast access, slow middle insert
    array           – Fixed-size, stack allocated, safer C array
    deque           – Fast push/pop front & back
    list            – Doubly linked, fast insert/delete, no random access
    forward_list    – Singly linked, low memory
    set             – Sorted unique values (RB-tree)
    multiset        – Sorted, allows duplicates
    unordered_set   – Hash set, fast lookup, no order
    map             – Sorted key-value pairs
    multimap        – Sorted map, duplicate keys
    unordered_map   – Hash map, fastest key lookup
    stack           – LIFO container adapter
    queue           – FIFO container adapter
    priority_queue  – Heap, fast max/min access

Iterators
    Input           – Read once (streams)
    Forward         – Multi-pass forward
    Bidirectional   – Forward & backward
    Random access   – [], +, - (vector, deque)

Algorithms
    find        – Linear search
    find_if     – Search with condition
    count_if    – Count matching elements
    sort        – Fast sort (O(n log n))
    stable_sort – Sort preserving order
    transform   – Apply function on range
    accumulate  – Reduce values
    copy        – Copy range
    remove_if   – Logical delete (needs erase)
    unique      – Remove consecutive duplicates
    lower_bound – First ≥ value (sorted)
    upper_bound – First > value

Utilities
    pair        – Two related values
    tuple       – Multiple heterogenous values
    optional    – Value or nothing
    variant     – One of many types
    any         – Any type (avoid in systems)
    function    – Callable wrapper
    bind        – Function binding (old style)

Time & Threads
    chrono      – Type-safe time
    thread      – OS thread
    mutex       – Mutual exclusion
    lock_guard  – RAII lock
    future      – Async result

Filesystem (C++17)
    path                – Portable file path
    directory_iterator  – Traverse directory
    exists              – Check file existence

Memory
    unique_ptr  – Exclusive ownership
    shared_ptr  – Reference counted
    weak_ptr    – Non-owning observer

Functions
    Lambda  – Inline anonymous function
    Functor – Object callable

Interview Fast Recall
    Cache           → list + unordered_map
    Fast lookup     → unordered_map
    Ordered data    → map / set
    Scheduler       → priority_queue
    Optional value  → std::optional